  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "It is a good time for moonshots.\n\nAI has reached a level where there are transformative projects that could result in huge social good, but require public R&amp;D, consensus &amp; transparency to pull off. Examples: universal tutors, co-scientist/replication systems, remote medical help.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2066534666257973523",
    "time": "2026-06-15 22:53",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 14:53:53 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066534666257973523",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Current open models are now good enough to pull off some of these projects if scaffolded properly while others (co-scientist) benefit from the AI frontier.\n\nBecause of that, this is an area where nations without frontier labs could contribute to the impact of AI for public good.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
